#: ../../source/help/apps/desktop-guide.rst:90
msgid "Bounce the Dock icon when receiving a notification (Mac only)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/apps/desktop-guide.rst:88
msgid ""
"When enabled, the Dock icon will either bounce once or bounce until the "
"user opens the app when receiving a notification."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/apps/desktop-guide.rst:95
msgid "Show Mattermost icon in the menu bar (Mac only)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/apps/desktop-guide.rst:93
msgid "When enabled, Mattermost icon is added to the Mac menu bar."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/apps/desktop-guide.rst:100
msgid "Show icon in the notification area (Linux only)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/apps/desktop-guide.rst:98
msgid "When enabled, Mattermost icon is added to the Linux notification area."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/apps/desktop-guide.rst:105
msgid ""
"Leave app running in notification center when application window is "
"closed (Linux only)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/apps/desktop-guide.rst:103
msgid ""
"When enabled, closing the application window will leave the Mattermost "
"desktop app running in your notification center. This can be useful if "
"you want to check for unread mentions while away from the app."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/apps/desktop-guide.rst:109
msgid "Use GPU hardware acceleration"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/apps/desktop-guide.rst:108
msgid ""
"If enabled, Mattermost UI is rendered more efficiently but can lead to "
"decreased stability for some systems. Setting takes effect after "
"restarting the app."
